00:35:47,170 --> 00:35:48,605
(flatline tone beeping)

00:35:48,671 --> 00:35:50,240
<i>She stroked out.</i>

00:35:50,306 --> 00:35:52,075
<i>It wasn't my fault.</i>

00:35:52,142 --> 00:35:54,878
They never should've
put the oxygen line there.

00:35:54,944 --> 00:35:56,579
They let me
off for that,

00:35:56,646 --> 00:35:59,949
but I didn't think anyone
would believe me this time.

00:36:00,016 --> 00:36:01,551
You were never convicted
of killing your grandmother.

00:36:01,618 --> 00:36:03,386
No.
Which is why you don't
have a record.

00:36:03,453 --> 00:36:05,188
You would've found out
eventually

00:36:05,255 --> 00:36:06,656
and held it against me.

00:36:06,723 --> 00:36:09,092
All right,
what about your neighbor?

00:36:09,159 --> 00:36:13,029
Mrs. Ivanovna-- did you kill
her or was that an accident?

00:36:13,096 --> 00:36:14,998
I just wanted to talk to her.

00:36:19,335 --> 00:36:21,871
MAX:
<i>You know, I thought</i>
<i>I could make it be okay.</i>

00:36:25,875 --> 00:36:27,644
Mrs. Ivanovna?

00:36:27,711 --> 00:36:28,945
Hello.

00:36:29,012 --> 00:36:29,979
Hello.

00:36:30,046 --> 00:36:30,980
What do you want?

00:36:31,047 --> 00:36:32,115
Good morning.

00:36:32,182 --> 00:36:34,851
Uh, I was wondering if I
might borrow some sugar.

00:36:37,887 --> 00:36:38,822
I get sugar.

00:36:38,888 --> 00:36:39,856
You stay.

00:36:39,923 --> 00:36:40,857
Sure.

00:36:40,924 --> 00:36:42,559
I get sugar.

00:36:42,625 --> 00:36:43,760
Stay!
Yeah.

00:36:43,827 --> 00:36:45,195
I get.
Yes.

00:36:45,261 --> 00:36:46,329
I get. You stay.

00:36:46,396 --> 00:36:50,166
I can't have my coffee
without my sugar.

00:36:50,233 --> 00:36:54,204
<i>The last thing I wanted to do</i>
<i>was hurt that lady.</i>

00:36:54,270 --> 00:36:56,539
Mrs. Ivanovna,
it's not what you think!

00:36:56,606 --> 00:36:59,376
No, Mrs. Ivanovna,
it's not what you think.

00:36:59,442 --> 00:37:00,877
You don't understand.
It was an accident.

00:37:02,579 --> 00:37:03,780
Mrs. Ivanovna?

00:37:03,847 --> 00:37:06,850
<i>She was dead.</i>

00:37:06,916 --> 00:37:10,086
<i>So, you know, I thought...</i>

00:37:12,722 --> 00:37:16,726
<i>maybe I'd make it</i>
<i>look like a suicide.</i>

00:37:19,295 --> 00:37:22,198
(sighs)

00:37:22,265 --> 00:37:24,934
It was not...

00:37:25,001 --> 00:37:26,903
a good start to the day.

00:37:26,970 --> 00:37:29,172
♪ ♪

00:37:58,668 --> 00:38:01,438
Don't eat that!

00:38:01,504 --> 00:38:04,140
After Suzy went back
to her mother,

00:38:04,207 --> 00:38:07,277
I decided to, you know...

00:38:07,343 --> 00:38:10,246
What, to give your wife--
your beloved wife--

00:38:10,313 --> 00:38:11,414
a proper burial?

00:38:11,481 --> 00:38:13,950
Something like that.

00:38:16,386 --> 00:38:19,389
<i>But along the way,</i>
<i>I had a bit of car trouble.</i>

00:38:20,990 --> 00:38:22,992
♪ ♪

00:38:38,842 --> 00:38:42,078
Few hours later,
some punk wanders over

00:38:42,145 --> 00:38:44,514
and swiped my wallet.

00:38:44,581 --> 00:38:46,316
That's my life.

00:38:46,383 --> 00:38:48,618
That's who I am.

00:38:48,685 --> 00:38:51,588
I'm the guy who
buys his daughter

00:38:51,654 --> 00:38:54,257
a puppy for her eighth birthday,

00:38:54,324 --> 00:38:58,094
and the next day, he backs out
of the driveway and...

00:39:01,097 --> 00:39:03,500
BRASS:
No. No.

00:39:03,566 --> 00:39:05,835
Don't tell me
you ran over the puppy.

00:39:05,902 --> 00:39:07,937
MAX:
No.

00:39:08,004 --> 00:39:10,206
I ran over my daughter.

00:39:10,273 --> 00:39:12,642
20 years later,
she still walks funny.

00:39:12,709 --> 00:39:14,711
(stifled laughter)

00:39:19,883 --> 00:39:21,284
(laughing):
I'm sorry.

00:39:21,351 --> 00:39:22,686
It's horrible.

00:39:22,752 --> 00:39:24,120
But it's really funny.

00:39:24,187 --> 00:39:25,221
(laughing)

00:39:25,288 --> 00:39:26,923
It's horrible
and it's funny.

00:39:29,959 --> 00:39:31,661
Are you okay?

00:39:33,697 --> 00:39:36,800
A guy kills two people
before breakfast

00:39:36,866 --> 00:39:38,401
that he had no intention
of killing

00:39:38,468 --> 00:39:40,437
when he woke up that morning.

00:39:40,503 --> 00:39:42,338
By all accounts,
he's led a meager life,

00:39:42,405 --> 00:39:43,740
an unnoticed life.

00:39:43,807 --> 00:39:46,676
And then all of
a sudden, in a flash,

00:39:46,743 --> 00:39:48,678
it's over.

00:39:48,745 --> 00:39:51,247
And now, for him,

00:39:51,314 --> 00:39:54,551
the real suffering begins.

00:39:54,617 --> 00:39:57,287
You're tired.

00:39:59,322 --> 00:40:01,991
Yeah.

00:40:02,058 --> 00:40:03,059
SIDLE:
Hey.

00:40:03,126 --> 00:40:04,694
Guess what.

00:40:04,761 --> 00:40:06,763
Mankind has reached
a new evolutionary plateau,

00:40:06,830 --> 00:40:10,600
and starting tomorrow, no one
will rape, murder or maim again.

00:40:10,667 --> 00:40:12,936
Uh, no.

00:40:13,002 --> 00:40:14,804
Too bad.

00:40:18,074 --> 00:40:20,510
But we did catch a break on that
disposable cell phone number.

00:40:20,577 --> 00:40:23,546
Raymundo Suarez
called it as well.

00:40:23,613 --> 00:40:24,914
No, he didn't.

00:40:24,981 --> 00:40:27,584
But according to the carrier,
additional minutes were

00:40:27,650 --> 00:40:30,620
recently purchased with a credit
card belonging to Ernie Dell.

00:40:33,323 --> 00:40:34,357
Brass is already on it.

00:40:34,424 --> 00:40:35,892
They're picking him up.

00:40:35,959 --> 00:40:39,763
We've got the
miniature killer.

00:40:39,829 --> 00:40:41,831
♪ ♪

00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:00,550
(beep)

00:41:00,617 --> 00:41:02,619
RECORDED VOICE:
You have new messages.

00:41:26,643 --> 00:41:29,579
My name is Ernest Edward Dell.

00:41:29,646 --> 00:41:32,449
I was born in 1946

00:41:32,515 --> 00:41:35,285
in Ames, Iowa.

00:41:35,352 --> 00:41:38,521
My life's been hard,
but I don't complain.

00:41:38,588 --> 00:41:41,524
I never expected better.

00:41:50,700 --> 00:41:53,203
I'm good with my hands.

00:41:53,269 --> 00:41:55,271
I make things. I fix things.

00:41:55,338 --> 00:41:56,373
I'm a handyman.

00:41:56,439 --> 00:41:58,408
That's what I am.

00:42:05,382 --> 00:42:09,285
A man has a right
to an honest day's pay.

00:42:09,352 --> 00:42:12,856
Me, I service
the machinery of death

00:42:12,922 --> 00:42:16,026
so that people can eat.

00:42:16,092 --> 00:42:19,229
If that makes me evil,
then so be it.

00:42:22,732 --> 00:42:26,503
I'm not the sociable type.
I know that.

00:42:26,569 --> 00:42:29,005
Spend any amount of time
around people,

00:42:29,072 --> 00:42:31,374
you get your heart broke.

00:42:31,441 --> 00:42:34,077
Treachery, hypocrisy.

00:42:36,079 --> 00:42:38,181
Promise of love.

00:42:41,051 --> 00:42:43,053
(model train running)

00:42:47,257 --> 00:42:50,894
Look into the mouth of a person,
and you'll find lies

00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:56,132
wriggling there like maggots
waiting to grow wings.

00:42:56,199 --> 00:42:59,502
The world has gone mad.

00:42:59,569 --> 00:43:03,206
A man could kill
from sunup to sunset,

00:43:03,273 --> 00:43:06,276
and still his work
would never be done.

